# This project does NOT need a build-time .env file —
# the frontend ships with public values in config.js, and
# the Edge Function gets its secrets injected by Supabase at runtime.
#
# This file exists only as a placeholder so the .gitignore line
# `.env` doesn't look like it refers to a missing concept.
#
# If you ever wire up build tooling (Vite/etc.), put values here
# and read them through that pipeline. Never commit real .env files.
